A: You can use a delimiter to separate the two strings. For example, you can use a newline character as a delimiter.
In the Client.java, you can send the two strings separated by a newline character:
outputStream.write(username.getText().getBytes());
outputStream.write("\n".getBytes());
outputStream.write(password.getText().getBytes());

In the Server.java, you can read the two strings separated by the newline character:
byte[] username = new byte[20];
inputStream.read(username);
String user = new String(username);

byte[] password = new byte[20];
inputStream.read(password);
String pass = new String(password);
